    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-07-11T16:47:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-07-11T16:47:00-05:00" n="218"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d218">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_FE1">FE</gloss> files, lot 55 D 128: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Joint Chiefs of Staff</gloss> to the
                        Commander in Chief Far East (<persName corresp="#p_CGMW1" type="to"
                            >Clark</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>operational immediate</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-07-11T17:47:00-04:00"
                            >July 11, 1952—5:47 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> 913383. From <gloss target="#t_JCS1"
                        >JCS</gloss>.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Action you propose in para 6 <gloss target="#t_C1">C</gloss> 51780<note
                            n="1" xml:id="d218fn1">
                            <hi rend="italic">
                                <ref target="#d218">Supra</ref>
                            </hi>.</note> is approved with understanding that method of presentation
                        to Communists of new round number of persons to be repatriated as outlined
                        in part 1 CX 51489<note n="2" xml:id="d218fn2">Dated July 7, <ref
                                target="#pg_380">p. 380</ref>.</note> should be modified as follows: <list>
                            <label>A.</label>
                            <item>Number of persons in each category should be presented only as
                                factual tabulation of results of completed UN screening. <gloss
                                    target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss> this approach will keep open
                                possibility that there may be some increase in total repatriated as
                                result of some form of post armistice interrogation.</item>
                            <label>B.</label>
                            <item>In reiterating proposals to permit individual interviews of
                                nonrepatriates ref should be made to an “impartial” rather than to a
                                “neutral” agency because of precedent established by our having
                                accepted Poland and Czechoslovakia as “neutrals” in Neutral Nations
                                Supervisory Commission. Use of word “impartial” would appear give us
                                greater negotiating latitude in arriving at an agency or group of
                                countries more acceptable to us for this purpose than one in which
                                there is satellite participation.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Decision on part 2 CX 51489 is being withheld pending development of
                        Communist reaction to foregoing presentation and outcome of discussions
                        between you and <persName corresp="#p_CGJL1">Gen Collins</persName>.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>There have been no further significant developments through channels<note
                            n="3" xml:id="d218fn3">The reference is to Government of India-People’s
                            Republic of China channels.</note> referred to in <gloss
                            target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> 911932.<note n="4" xml:id="d218fn4">Dated
                            June 23, <ref target="#pg_347">p. 347</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
